fields.title: One Direction: This Is Us
fields.review: Packed with nonstop energy and cheeky good fun!

fields.title: Sayap-Sayap Patah
fields.review: a film that has a fresh story, shows the life of Densus 88 which has never been shot before.

fields.title: Love, Rosie
fields.review: The best rom coms out there. Both the main actors have amazing chemistry.

fields.title: Mean Girls
fields.review: I may not be those 2000s american teens, but I could tell you this movie is captured reality and some relatable moments as a highschooler.

fields.title: Love, Simon
fields.review: a great coming of age/romance movie and it really made me think differently on things.

fields.title: The Conjuring
fields.review: Completes a modern supernatural horror film.

fields.title: Pengabdi Setan
fields.review: an underrated Asian horror gem. The plot is not new but the way it's executed makes it look fresh.

fields.title: Spiderman : No Way Home
fields.review: a masterpiece. It tells an amazing origin story about Peter Parker and how he became everyone's favorite Wall-Crawler.

fields.title: Pengabdi Setan 2 : Communion
fields.review: a more gripping sequel than the first film. Brings a complete package of haunted experiences.

fields.title: The Orphanage
fields.review: Absolutely brilliant film from start to finish. The main lady is superb.
